## 1. Design Tokens

> These values are the single source of truth for all visual decisions. No magic numbers in CSS.

### 1.1 Color Palette

| Token                    | Value         | Usage                                    |
|--------------------------|---------------|------------------------------------------|
| `--color-primary`        | `[hex]`       | Primary action buttons, highlights       |
| `--color-primary-hover`  | `[hex]`       | Hover state on primary actions           |
| `--color-surface`        | `[hex]`       | Card and panel backgrounds               |
| `--color-background`     | `[hex]`       | Page background                          |
| `--color-text-primary`   | `[hex]`       | Body text (≥4.5:1 contrast on surface)   |
| `--color-text-secondary` | `[hex]`       | Supporting / metadata text (≥3:1)        |
| `--color-border`         | `[hex]`       | Input borders, dividers                  |
| `--color-error`          | `[hex]`       | Error states (≥4.5:1 on white/surface)   |
| `--color-success`        | `[hex]`       | Success / confirmation states            |
| `--color-warning`        | `[hex]`       | Warning indicators                       |

> Contrast ratios must meet WCAG 2.2 AA (4.5:1 for normal text, 3:1 for large text / UI components). Validate with: [Who Can Use](https://www.whocanuse.com/) or [Colour Contrast Analyser](https://www.tpgi.com/color-contrast-checker/).

