## 5. Accessibility Rules (WCAG 2.2 AA)

| Rule                      | Standard     | Implementation note                                               |
|---------------------------|--------------|-------------------------------------------------------------------|
| Colour contrast — text    | 1.4.3 (AA)   | Normal text ≥4.5:1; large text ≥3:1                               |
| Colour contrast — UI      | 1.4.11 (AA)  | Interactive components and focus indicators ≥3:1                  |
| Focus visible             | 2.4.11 (AA)  | All interactive elements have visible focus ring (no `outline: none`) |
| Touch target size         | 2.5.8 (AA)   | Minimum 24×24 px; prefer 44×44 px                                 |
| Keyboard navigation       | 2.1.1        | All features operable by keyboard alone                           |
| Skip navigation           | 2.4.1        | "Skip to main content" link as first focusable element            |
| Form labels               | 1.3.1, 3.3.2 | Every input has explicit `<label>` or `aria-label`                |
| Error identification       | 3.3.1        | Errors described in text (not colour alone)                       |
| Language                  | 3.1.1        | `<html lang="th">` or `"en"` as appropriate                       |
| Reflow                    | 1.4.10       | Content reflows at 320 px width without horizontal scroll         |
| Motion / animation        | 2.3.3        | Respect `prefers-reduced-motion`                                  |

